  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Tasks/ Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Ensure that project execution strategies comply with Boskalis Safety, Health, Environment, and Quality (SHE-Q) standards, and take corrective action where necessary. Actively foster a culture of safety and operational excellence</li><li>Monitor and support ongoing projects through frequent site visits, regular reporting, and strong information flows with relevant team members, taking action to address operational shortcomings.</li><li>Lead, coach, and develop the operations (support) team to drive high performance, coordination, and professional growth.</li><li>Develop and contribute specialist salvage expertise to safe and effective execution methods, including advising on equipment, vessels, and operational approaches.</li><li>Support tendering and acquisition processes by providing operational input.</li><li>Ensure effective staffing and resource allocation for projects in consultation with the Operations Director Salvage.</li><li>Build and maintain a strong operational response network to ensure rapid, effective mobilization of resources worldwide.</li><li>Encourage and maintain strong flow of information to and from the Operations Director Salvage and Salvage Masters, supporting knowledge sharing, project monitoring, and optimization.</li></ul><p><u><strong>REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE / EXPERIENCE</strong></u></p><p><strong>Education/certificates:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent Higher Professional Education in a technical, maritime or nautical </li></ul><p><strong>Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Extensive experience in the Oil & Gas/Maritime Salvage industry</li><li>Proven experience in project, financial, contractual, and risk management within complex operational environments</li><li>Strong people management skills with demonstrated ability to lead diverse teams and work effectively across different cultures</li></ul><p><strong>Other requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Willingness and ability to respond immediately to salvage requests, including frequent international travel and deployments at short notice</li></ul>",
